;; === cons_corruption_repro.aura ===
;;
;; REGRESSION TEST for the string/keyword tag overlap bug.
;; 
;; === ROOT CAUSE (found 2026-06-04) ===
;;
;; The tag scheme has a collision between STRING_BIAS - idx and RefKeyword
;; bit patterns. For idx values where (STRING_BIAS - idx) has bit 0 = 1
;; AND bits 2-5 = 11 (= RefKeyword type), the value passes BOTH is_string()
;; AND is_keyword() checks. The display path checked is_keyword FIRST,
;; so legitimate strings at idx 19, 83, 147, ... were misdisplayed as
;; fake RefKeywords (":147605376151711743").
;;
;; Trigger: any string at the collision indices, the most common one
;; being idx 19 in a typical test. The reason earlier investigation
;; required a specific 4-call sequence was just to land the string
;; "hello" at exactly that idx.
;;
;; === FIX (commit pending) ===
;;
; Reorder display checks in io_print_val (evaluator_impl.cpp) and
; format_value (evaluator.ixx) so is_string is checked BEFORE is_keyword.
; For overlapping values, the string interpretation wins (and in
; practice, no real RefKeyword has such a huge index).
;
;; === VERIFICATION ===
;;
; Run with:  ./build/aura < tests/cons_corruption_repro.aura
; Expected (after fix): r4=hello

(require std/safe-refactor all:)

;; Trigger the bug: 4 calls, r1+r2+r3 trigger 2 ast:restores, r4 returns a string
(define r1 (safe-refactor:with-snapshot "repro-t1" (lambda () 42)))
(define r2 (safe-refactor:with-snapshot "repro-t2" (lambda () (error "boom"))))
(define r3 (safe-refactor:with-snapshot "repro-t3" (lambda () 'fail)))
(define r4 (safe-refactor:with-snapshot "repro-t4" (lambda () "hello")))

(display "r4=") (display r4) (newline)
;; expect: r4=hello
